<HL>
   Who's News:
   Pitney Bowes Realigns
   Officers in New Units
</HL>
<DATE>
05/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   PBI WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   STAMFORD, Conn. -- Pitney Bowes Inc. named four officers
to head new units in what the business equipment, supplies
and financial services company called a "strategic
realignment."
   Hiro R. Hiranandani, 52 years old, previously president,
business systems, international unit, was appointed
president, mailing systems, a new unit combining U.S. and
international operations. Mr. Hiranandani succeeds James L.
Bast, 54, formerly president, U.S. business systems, who left
the company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Carole F. St. Mark, 47, formerly president, business
supplies and services, was named president, logistics systems
and business services.
   Marc C. Breslawsky, 47, formerly vice president and chief
executive officer, Dictaphone Corp. and facsimile and copier
systems, was appointed president, office systems.
   Douglas A. Riggs, 45, formerly vice president, corporate
communications and external affairs, was named vice
president, corporate planning, communications and external
affairs.
</TEXT>
